CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 13, 1956, pg. A7 reads: "New Dishes For Home - Members of the Kolesque Club donated a 104-piece set of dishes to the Aged Ministers and Laymen's Home at 605 Oakwood St. Presenting the dishes, left to right, are Mrs. Adelaide Montgomery, Odell King, president; Mrs. Ruth Perry, matron at home; Mrs. Kathleen Hurst and MRs. Geraldine Gilbert.  There are nine other members in the club. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Kolesque Club members, from left: Adelaide Montgomery, Odell King, Ruth Perry, Kathleen Hurst, and Geraldine Gilbert, packaging place settings for donation, in interior with floral curtains
